Review_Text: The current version of the app has a very poor user experience, it is very unresponsive. It also has other UX issues. "Me" -> "Home" (3.5s)  "Me" -> "Me/Accounts" (3.5s)  In addition, when loading the "Me/Accounts" page of the app, it takes a another 3 seconds to be able to scroll down to see your other accounts. Is this a separate query because you've used paginated data or something?  I've noticed the "material" animation on the button always finishes before navigation happens, I hope the app is not waiting for animations to finish before issuing queries? I say this because it happens even for pages that do not have to load data, like "Me" -> "Me/Insurance"  The back arrow does not have any activation animation, together with the unresponsiveness it's hard to know if you've managed to tap it or not.  The transaction list and transaction detail view: Most transaction comments are truncated, tapping on it to go into the detail view does not help because it is not visible.  That's all that I can fit in this review.
